text.config.onmymark.option.blockMarkerL:
Determines how long the block marker will stay on your screen, in seconds.
This value is overriden by the server.
text.config.onmymark.option.circleClampD:
Determines how large the circle clamp should be.
A larger value will cause the circle to be larger, and is limited
by the Minecraft screen size.
text.config.onmymark.option.distanceLabe: Determines how large the distance label should be.
text.config.onmymark.option.entityMarker:
Determines how long the entity marker will stay on your screen, in seconds.
This value is overriden by the server.
text.config.onmymark.option.markerClampT:
Determines how clamped markers are drawn.
For example, the default Oval clamp type will draw any markers
that are out of bounds along the circumference of an oval.
text.config.onmymark.option.markerPointe: Determines how tall the pointer should be.
Determines how wide the pointer should be.
text.config.onmymark.option.isPlayerHead:
Determines whether the player who placed the marker should have their head
drawn alongside the marker.
text.config.onmymark.option.playerHeadSc: Determines the size of the player head drawn.
text.config.onmymark.option.ovalClampPad:
Determines how padded you prefer the oval clamp to be.
A larger value will cause the oval to be smaller in size, and vice versa.
text.config.onmymark.option.playerMarker:
Determines how long the player's marker will stay on your screen (when a player reports in), in seconds.
This value is overriden by the server.
text.config.onmymark.title: On My Mark Configuration
